Plan Frontend Specifications
After your mentor approves of your capstone project proposal, you will plan the frontend control
flow along with User Interface components. There are many ways to plan out your frontend
control flow, it may be tedious but planning is important as it allows us to plan our logic and
ensure our application works in our intended manner. A good logical flow will also allow us to
(hopefully) write more maintainable and scalable code. With a good, planned control flow we
can split up our workload into small, manageable tasks and use our time efficiently.
Let’s take a look back at our example, a “Facebook for Dogs (and their Owners)” take a look at
how the very basic control flow of an application like this can be planned out:
Example on How to Make a Flow Diagram:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cvYhuowazh0
Example Frontend Application flow chart:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/10IgW75PdaIi2fO0Jo43s8lAvaWUcqAQu/view?usp=sharing
Note: You are welcome to use any popular free tools such as Figma, or StarUML or if you are
comfortable in any other tools (Sketch, Illustrator, Photoshop) you are welcome to use them as
well.
Feel free to share the link with the mentor so that they can review your flow diagram. You do not
need formal approval from your mentor to continue working on the project, but they will probably
have advice that can help you